the house for further reflection...

9
00:01:17,604 --> 00:01:19,196
and a little nosh.

10
00:02:13,292 --> 00:02:15,657
I got rid of the couch.

11
00:02:40,718 --> 00:02:43,346
You are so strong.

12
00:02:43,854 --> 00:02:48,449
Just like at your father's service.
You didn't cry then either.

13
00:02:49,426 --> 00:02:51,360
I was two.

14
00:02:51,928 --> 00:02:55,261
Well, children are keenly
aware of death.

15
00:02:55,465 --> 00:02:58,957
You were my own little
John-John Kennedy.

16
00:03:09,879 --> 00:03:13,076
-What is she doing here?
-Who?

17
00:03:14,484 --> 00:03:16,076
Your aunt.

18
00:03:19,021 --> 00:03:22,889
Troy. Please!
She'll ruin everything.

19
00:03:24,493 --> 00:03:26,893
How do you ruin a funeral?

20
00:03:32,701 --> 00:03:34,635
I wasn't sure whether or not
you were coming.

21
00:03:34,837 --> 00:03:37,897
Of course. I loved that girl.

22
00:03:38,107 --> 00:03:39,335
Just didn't wanna waste
such a beautiful day...

23
00:03:39,541 --> 00:03:41,702
listening to a bunch
of medieval mumbo-jumbo.

24
00:03:41,910 --> 00:03:44,470
Actually, you know,
the service was pretty nice.

25
00:03:44,680 --> 00:03:48,582
Please! The last time you two were
in church was the day you got married.

26
00:03:48,784 --> 00:03:50,718
And you only did that
to appease Morticia.

27
00:03:50,953 --> 00:03:52,010
Hilda.

28
00:03:53,454 --> 00:03:56,719
-What are you doing?
-I'm planting a testimonial.

29
00:03:57,024 --> 00:04:01,021
-It's a cactus.
-They were all out of eternal flames.

30
00:04:03,798 --> 00:04:07,825
Troy, I'm very overwhelmed
right now.

31
00:04:08,603 --> 00:04:11,868
I will see you inside in a minute.
Let me...

32
00:04:19,714 --> 00:04:22,945
When isn't she very overwhelmed?

33
00:04:23,550 --> 00:04:25,211
Come on inside...

34
00:04:25,886 --> 00:04:27,615
when you're finished.

35
00:04:36,730 --> 00:04:42,362
Just remember, Troy:
peace I leave with you.

36
00:04:42,969 --> 00:04:46,336
Let not your heart be troubled.

37
00:04:49,776 --> 00:04:51,835
So said John.

38
00:05:04,623 --> 00:05:06,523
John who?

39
00:05:07,660 --> 00:05:09,457
Bible John.

40
00:05:10,229 --> 00:05:13,130
Right. Yeah. He was cool.

41
00:05:15,467 --> 00:05:18,459
So, how're you doing?

42
00:05:19,305 --> 00:05:21,364
-I'm okay.
-Good.

43
00:05:21,574 --> 00:05:24,543
Good. Good.

44
00:05:29,647 --> 00:05:33,606
So listen, I was thinking.
We should take a trip. Maybe Vegas.

45
00:05:34,152 --> 00:05:35,744
We've been talking
about going since college.

46
00:05:35,954 --> 00:05:38,582
-No, man. I need to work.
-Come on, man. Just for the weekend.

47
00:05:38,790 --> 00:05:41,258
It, it's good to take a trip
after a loss.

48
00:05:44,395 --> 00:05:46,329
So what are you supposed
to do after a win?

49
00:05:56,808 --> 00:05:58,537
So this is dreary.

50
00:05:59,611 --> 00:06:03,512
-Anybody have a good story?
-Story about what?

51
00:06:04,181 --> 00:06:07,480
