You know, I've never met anyone
who was so happy being so miserable.

78
00:07:32,734 --> 00:07:35,168
-Walk me out?
-Yeah.

79
00:07:37,671 --> 00:07:39,502
Just wait a second.

80
00:07:43,477 --> 00:07:46,605
I thought the viewing was nice.

81
00:07:48,215 --> 00:07:53,312
You know, you really should get away
from all this sanctimonious bullshit.

82
00:07:53,520 --> 00:07:56,045
Give yourself some room to breathe.

83
00:07:56,690 --> 00:07:59,591
My desert's beautiful
this time of year.

84
00:08:00,094 --> 00:08:02,085
I'll think about it.

85
00:08:02,296 --> 00:08:05,288
-Can't ask for more than that.
-Nope.

86
00:08:08,602 --> 00:08:10,728
She wanted me to give this to you.

87
00:08:22,248 --> 00:08:23,408
Okay.

88
00:09:13,597 --> 00:09:14,859
Troy.

89
00:09:15,833 --> 00:09:17,300
Troy!

90
00:09:17,501 --> 00:09:19,093
Mr. Hutchinson. Hi.

91
00:09:19,303 --> 00:09:23,296
Well, I was just wondering
how you were feeling.

92
00:09:24,341 --> 00:09:27,071
Thank you, sir.
I'm gonna be okay.

93
00:09:27,645 --> 00:09:30,113
Maybe you would like
to take a few days off.

94
00:09:30,314 --> 00:09:33,806
-You know, too rest.
-No, really, sir. I'm okay.

95
00:09:34,018 --> 00:09:38,682
I actually feel really good just,
you know, being back at work.

96
00:09:38,889 --> 00:09:44,020
There's nothing like good, hard work
to take a man's mind off his troubles.

97
00:09:44,929 --> 00:09:48,921
So, how is the Boyle project
coming along?

98
00:09:49,132 --> 00:09:51,293
Well, sir, yeah.
Very, very well.

99
00:09:51,501 --> 00:09:55,460
Well, it's crunch-time on that one.
We present in a week, so...

100
00:10:08,384 --> 00:10:09,976
Alright.
So where are we going to lunch?

101
00:10:10,186 --> 00:10:13,519
You're going to lunch.
I'm staying here.

102
00:10:13,723 --> 00:10:15,918
Come on, sushi place down the street.
I'll buy the sake.

103
00:10:16,125 --> 00:10:17,558
No, man. I'm not hungry.
Thank you.

104
00:10:17,759 --> 00:10:19,249
