192
00:19:05,771 --> 00:19:07,329
Oh, man.

193
00:19:10,342 --> 00:19:13,311
-She's a little girl.
-Is there a problem?

194
00:19:14,113 --> 00:19:16,138
It's a girl.

195
00:19:17,216 --> 00:19:18,808
What do you know about that!

196
00:19:19,151 --> 00:19:23,383
Thank you.
You did so good.

197
00:19:24,523 --> 00:19:26,820
You did good.
Real good.

198
00:19:27,024 --> 00:19:28,423
Son, you gonna let us
get outta here?

199
00:19:28,626 --> 00:19:31,789
That kid's gonna be talking
before I can get her to a doctor.

200
00:19:31,996 --> 00:19:33,554
Bye-bye.

201
00:20:30,953 --> 00:20:32,580
-Who is it?
-Hey, it's me.

202
00:20:32,788 --> 00:20:34,813
-Who's me?
-I'm sorry. It's Troy.

203
00:20:35,024 --> 00:20:36,548
Troy!

204
00:20:37,126 --> 00:20:39,060
Hi, I'm sorry. I tried calling you
a couple of times...

205
00:20:39,261 --> 00:20:40,660
but you don't have a machine, so...

206
00:20:40,863 --> 00:20:44,299
Oh, yeah. Usually if it's important
they call back or they just show up.

207
00:20:44,500 --> 00:20:45,728
-Where's your stuff?
-It's all in the car.

208
00:20:45,935 --> 00:20:47,334
You know, I'll get it later.

209
00:20:47,536 --> 00:20:49,333
You know, I thought
about what you said...

210
00:20:49,538 --> 00:20:50,766
about getting away and everything.

211
00:20:50,973 --> 00:20:53,635
Stop shoveling.
It was Corrine's letter.

212
00:20:53,843 --> 00:20:56,903
Don't worry. I don't take things
as personally as most people.

213
00:20:57,112 --> 00:20:58,477
Did you read the letter?

214
00:20:59,982 --> 00:21:01,609
She wrote it to you.

215
00:21:01,817 --> 00:21:05,809
This is the guest room and...
clean towels in the closet.

216
00:21:06,020 --> 00:21:08,545
